The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Derby to be held in city 

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: The East Bengal-Mohun Bagan derby clash will now be held in the city on April 9. There was some uncertainty over the IFA hosting a few matches because of the state elections during that time. 

The state government on Wednesday allowed National Football League matches to be held in the city till April 15, according to IFA secretary Subrata Dutta. 

The IFA has in turn suggested to the AIFF that Calcutta teams matches after April 15 be held in Jamshedpur. Earlier, New Delhi, Bangalore and Calicut were being thought of as possible venues. 




